CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 3, 1945, pg. 17, reads: "Honor Daughter-In-Law - Mrs. and Mrs. John Strong, 2706 Bedford Avenue, honored their daughter-in-law, Mrs. Delois Strong, of Baltimore, Md., who is the wife of their son, 1st Lieut. John W. Strong, serving in the South Pacific. Those present at the party were, left to right: James Bailey, Florence Perry, Linsay Perry, Lee Clark, Betty Stokes, Robert Henderson, Thomas Sumpter, Mary Ellis and Pepper Davis. Seated, left to right, are: Louise Couch, Delois Strong and Lucille Strong. Those nor shown in the picture are June Hamilton, Roderick Robinson and Phillip Kiszie. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Guests at party in home of of John Strong, standing from left: James Bailey, Florence Perry, Linsay Perry, Lee Clark, Betty Stokes, Robert Henderson, Thomas Sumpter, Mary Ellis and Pepper Davis; seated: Louise Couch, Delois Strong and Lucille Strong posed in front of mantle with photographs, 2706 Bedford Avenue, Hill District
